    "imgUrl": "/public/images/2018/03/00.png",
    "sectionHeading": "What is an API?",
    "text": "An 'application programming interface' (API) is a set of actions, templates, and tools for interacting with software. One such example is the Web API and will be the focus on this guide. A web API will allow the user to make HTTP(s) calls to a web service and get back some data in return; typically JSON or XML."
  },
  {
    "id": 1,
    "imgUrl": "/public/images/2018/03/01.png",
    "sectionHeading": "What Do I Use to Test?",
    "text": "You can use anything capable of building, sending, and receiving HTTP(s) requests. This guide will use PostMan, a popular GUI based product."
  },
  {
    "id": 2,
    "imgUrl": "/public/images/2018/03/02.png",
    "sectionHeading": "What Do I Test?",
    "text": "Start with C.R.U.D. operations using thier correlated HTTP Verb. Create a record by POSTing one. Read a record using a GET. Update a record using PUT. Delete the record using DELETE."
  },
